{"lemma":"وَسَطٌ","slug":"وَسَطٌ","root":"#.س.ط","root_slug":"_-س-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/_-س-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"وَسَطٌ","root":"وسط","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41936"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"middle, center"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"waist"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the golden mean"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"milieu, environment, surroundings, sphere"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"means, instrument, agent, medium"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mediocrity, medium quality, average"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"circles, quarters, classes, strata (of population)","tags":["in-plural"]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"amidst, midst, at the center of, in the middle of, among, amongst"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be in the middle, to penetrate into the middle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to place or put in the middle"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine plural of أَوْسَط (ʔawsaṭ)","tags":["feminine","form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Classical Syriac ܝܫܛܐ (yašṭā, “esophagus, throat”) and Ge'ez ውሳጤ (wəsaṭe, “inside, interior”)."},"ipa":["/wa.satˤ/","/wastˤ/","/wa.sa.tˤa/","/was.sa.tˤa/","/wu.satˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41936","headword_ar":"وَسَطٌ","root":"wsT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle, midst,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; i. e.,] properly, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of which several lateral,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outer, portions are equal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as, for instance, the middle finger: but also meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part which is surrounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enclosed, on its several sides, although unequally:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that is between the two sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremities"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; (M, IB, Mgh, K;) [or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point, that is between every two opposite extremities"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; and properly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when equidistant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as, for instance, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"centre"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a circle: (Mgh:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTu","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which is [likewise] a subst., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afokalN","text_ar":"اَفْكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azomalN","text_ar":"اَزْمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but imperfectly decl. because originally an epithet]: (M:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaTN","text_ar":"وَسَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has its middle letter with fet-h in order that it may agree in measure with its contr., which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TarafN","text_ar":"طَرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the like agreement being frequent: (IB:) and it is only used in cases in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona","text_ar":"بَيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may not be substituted for it, herein [and in other respects, mentioned in the next preceding paragraph,] differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasoT","text_ar":"وَسْط"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, IB, K:) [respecting the similar and dissimilar usages of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaT","text_ar":"وَسَط"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"was~T","text_ar":"وَسّط"},{"kind":"text","text":", sufficient observations have been made in the next preceding paragraph, which see throughout, and more especially in its latter part:] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaTN","text_ar":"وَسَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaATN","text_ar":"اَوْسَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that of its syn. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTu","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awaAsiTu","text_ar":"اَوَاسِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or this may be a pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAsiTN","text_ar":"وَاسِطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wawaAsiTu","text_ar":"وَوَاسِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasotu fiY","text_ar":"جَلَسْتُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaTi Ald~aAri","text_ar":"وَسَطِ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sat in the middle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle part, of the house"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Mgh, Msb;) because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaT","text_ar":"وَسَط"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a subst. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_it~asaEa wasaTuhu","text_ar":"اـِتَّسَعَ وَسَطُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The middle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle part, thereof, became wide"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Darabotu wasaTa raA^osihi","text_ar":"ضَرَبْتُ وَسَطَ رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I smote the middle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle part, of his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh, * Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasarotu wasaTa Alr~umoHi","text_ar":"كَسَرْتُ وَسَطَ الرُّمْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I broke the middle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle part, of the spear"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IB.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaTuhu xayorN mino Tarafihi","text_ar":"وَسَطُهُ خَيْرٌ مِنْ طَرَفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The middle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle part, thereof is better than the extremity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayaru AlA^umuwri A^awosaATuhaA","text_ar":"خَيَرُ الاُمُورِ اَوْسَاطُهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The best of affairs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"actions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cases, are such of them as are between two extremes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M. [See R. Q. 1, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hq","text_ar":"حق"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) It is sometimes put in the accus. case as an adv. n.; as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasotu","text_ar":"جَلَسْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaTa Ald~aAri","text_ar":"وَسَطَ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is an instance of departure from the original usage; and [the meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasotu fiY wasaTi Ald~aAri","text_ar":"جَلَسْتُ فِى وَسَطِ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying as explained above; so that] it is not here syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona","text_ar":"بَيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasoTa","text_ar":"وَسْطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is. (IB.) ―         -b2-  It is also used as an epithet: (IB, Mgh:) [as such signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Middle; intermediate; midway,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equidistant, between the two extremities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremes; in place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"position:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but in this sense superseded in usage by ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTu","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAsiTN","text_ar":"وَاسِطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutawas~iTN","text_ar":"مُتَوَسِّطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but in this sense also superseded in usage by ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTu","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middling; of middle sort, kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTu","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutawas~iTN","text_ar":"مُتَوَسِّطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasuwTN","text_ar":"وَسُوطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasiyTN","text_ar":"وَسِيطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between good and bad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTu","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conforming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conformable, to the just mean; just; equitable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, M, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasiyTN","text_ar":"وَسِيطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most conforming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conformable, to the just mean; most just; most equitable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to what is so of a thing; (S, M, K;) whatever it be; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTa","text_ar":"اَوْسَطَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTu","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, * Msb, K *:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most generous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and when used as an epithet, it is applied alike to a masc., fem., sing., dual, and pl., subst.: (Mgh:) the fem. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTu","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wusoTaY","text_ar":"وُسْطَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;) and the pl. masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awaAsiTu","text_ar":"اَوَاسِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and pl. fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wusaTN","text_ar":"وُسَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) Hence, (Msb,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iSobaEu AlwusoTaY","text_ar":"الاـِصْبَعُ الوُسْطَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The middle finger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyawomu AlA^awosaTu","text_ar":"اليَوْمُ الاَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The middle day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayolapu AlwusoTaY","text_ar":"اللَّيْلَةُ الوُسْطَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The middle night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa$arapu AlA^awaAsiTu","text_ar":"العَشَرَةُ الاَوَاسِطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ten middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"days."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa$oru","text_ar":"العَشْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwusaTu","text_ar":"الوُسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ten middle nights:"},{"kind":"text","text":"not"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2942},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa$oru AlA^awosaTu","text_ar":"العَشْرُ الاَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for this is a vulgar mistake, into which relaters of traditions have fallen; or it may be a mistake of transcription. (Msb.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~al`wpu AlwusoTaY","text_ar":"الصَّلٰوةُ الوُسْطَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh, &c.,) mentioned in the Kur, [ii. 239,] (M, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The middle prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the other prayers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the prayers of the night and the day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the most excellent of them in particular:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of the afternoon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"('Alee Ibn-Abee-Tálib, I'Ab, and others, Mgh, Bd, K;) because the prophet said, on the day of the Ahzáb, “ they have diverted us from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlSlwp AlwsTY","text_ar":"الصلوة الوسطى"},{"kind":"text","text":", the prayer of the afternoon: ” (Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of daybreak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(also said to be on the authority of 'Alee, Mgh, Bd, K;) because it is between the prayers of the night and the day; (Bd;) for the saying of the prophet mentioned above does not contravene this and other assertions, since what is meant in the trad. is not what is meant in the Kur: (K:) or, (M, K,) accord. to Abu-l-Hasan, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of Friday;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) because it is the most excellent of the prayers; (M;) and he who says otherwise errs, unless he trace up the assertion to the prophet: (M, K:) these three opinions are of the strongest authority; (B;) and the first is that which commonly obtains: (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of noon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Bd, Msb, K;) because it is in the middle of the day: (Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of Friday on the day thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on other days the prayer of noon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, and also said to be on the authority of 'Alec:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of sunset:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Bd, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of nightfall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, K:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night-prayer called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwitor","text_ar":"الوِتْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of the breaking of the fast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of sacrifices:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of the period called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuHaY","text_ar":"ضُحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of the congregation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of fear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayers of nightfall and daybreak together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, and said to be on the authorities of 'Omar and 'Othmán:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayers of daybreak and the afternoon together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any of the five prayers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because before it are two prayers and after it are two prayers: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all the divinely-appointed prayers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain prayers not particularized:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prayer of middling length, between long and short."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) Hence also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaTN","text_ar":"وَسَطٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A middling thing; a thing of middle sort"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between good and bad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTu","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and in like manner it is applied to a male slave, and a female slave, (Msb,) and two male slaves, and two sheep or goats. (Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA tuToEimuwna","text_ar":"مَا تُطْعِمُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^awosaTi","text_ar":"مِنْ اَوْسَطِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholiykumo","text_ar":"اَهْلِيكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, [v. 91,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of the middle sort of that which ye give for food to your families,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between what is prodigal and what is niggardly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~amaTu AlA^awosaTu","text_ar":"النَّمَطُ الاَوْسَطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The middle class of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurring in a saying of 'Alee, cited in full in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gT","text_ar":"غط"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~imoniY","text_ar":"عَلِّمْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynFA wasuwTA","text_ar":"دِينًا وَسُوطا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Teach thou to me a religion of the middle sort:"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurring in a saying of an Arab of the desert to El-Hasan, cited in full voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraTa","text_ar":"فَرَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalonaAkumo A^am~apF wasaTFA","text_ar":"جَعَلْنَاكُمْ اَمَّةً وَسَطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, [ii. 137,] (S, Mgh, Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We have made you to be a nation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conforming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conformable, to the just mean; just; equitable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, S, IB, Bd, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, Bd, Msb, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroEFY","text_ar":"مَرْعًى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaTN","text_ar":"وَسَطٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Choice pasturage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN wasaTN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ وَسَطٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasiyTN","text_ar":"وَسِيطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man having good grounds of pretension to respect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY qawomihi","text_ar":"فِى قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN wasiyTN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ وَسِيطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K *,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumo","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in some copies of the K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the best of his people"},{"kind":"text","text":"(↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTuhumo","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in race, and the highest of them in station."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAri waAlHasabi","text_ar":"الدَّارِ وَالحَسَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN wasiyTu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ وَسِيطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of good quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the best quality, in respect of tribe, and of grounds of pretension to honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lth.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa mino wasaTi qawomihi","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنْ وَسَطِ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn A^awosaTihimo","text_ar":"من اَوْسَطِهِمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is of the best of his people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa mino wasaTi Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنْ وَسَطِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn A^awosaTihi","text_ar":"من اَوْسَطِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is of the best of the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAla","text_ar":"قَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTuhumo","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur, lxviii. 28,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The best of them said:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the most rightly directed, of them, to the truth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or it means ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awosaTuhumo","text_ar":"اَوْسَطُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oyFA","text_ar":"رَاْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the most remote, of them, from either extreme, in judgment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~FA","text_ar":"سِنًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in age"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Bd.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","Mgh","M","K","IB","S","TA","Zj","Bd","Jel"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}